article.headline: Hartford 78, Dartmouth 68
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. (AP) -- Ryan Stys scored 22 points and Aaron Cook had 21 as Hartford defeated Dartmouth 78-68 Friday night. Hartford (7-8) trailed Dartmouth (3-13) 56-55, and then went on a 14-2 run that decided the game. Cook's fifth 3-point basket gave the Hawks a 69-58 lead with 5:34 to play, and Dartmouth couldn't get closer than five down the stretch. The Big Green was led by Leon Pattman, who matched his career high of 29 points reached two days ago. In consecutive games, he scored more points than any other freshman in Dartmouth history. David Gardner added a career-high of 20 points.
